p: I H. G. Thornton, the Deputy officer to whom the within writ was directed state that I have been to find Ah Chow the said writ is directed and upon whom it was to be ordered, although I have duty and for him I further state now in person and belief that the said Ah Chow was dissharged from the County himself so that no can be of this writ
Subscribed & sworn to before me, January 23d 1874
